an class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>) →\n      <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₂</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">k₁</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₁</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₂</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₂</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">X₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">X₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>) →\n    <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k₁</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>) →\n      <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₂</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">k₁</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">X₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₂</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">X₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₁</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X₀</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">k₀</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">X₀</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">X₀</span> <span class=\"fn\">k₀</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Final.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.Initial.lift\">lift</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Final.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.Initial.homToLift\">homToLift</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We provide an induction principle for reasoning about `lift` and `homToLift`.\nWe want to perform some construction (usually just a proof) about\nthe particular choices `lift F d` and `homToLift F d`,\nit suffices to perform that construction for some other pair of choices\n(denoted `X₀ : C` and `k₀ : F.obj X₀ ⟶ d` below),\nand to show how to transport such a construction\n*both* directions along a morphism between such choices.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Final.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.Initial.induction","kind":"def","line":548,"name":"CategoryTheory.Functor.Initial.induction","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Final.lean#L548-L575"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Final.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.Initial.homToLift\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Functor</span>.<span class=\"name\">Initial</span>.<span class=\"name\">homToLift</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\